node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Running | Runners | Run on September 07, 2021 tagging @gigi_ultrarunner. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
by @Gigi_ultrarunner 💪 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process.

How does it feel to run 100 miles? Just look at my expression and you get your answer.

At 90 miles I was exhausted and in pain , but the determination to persevere had to prevail. It is a mind game. When your mind tells you "you are done", prove it wrong. 
You can always give it a little bit more. Shut your thoughts off and just keep moving. One step at a time. Stay focused. Stay in the moment. Trust yourself and your abilities, and always bring some extra snacks! 

Once you reach the finish line, everything subsides. No worries, no pain, no exhaustion .
Just a big smile and a happy heart. 

#ultrarunning #100miler #corunning

Never give up 👊 We can promote your photos in our account. Click the link in our bio for instructions: @RunningTerritory 

Leg day is always hard, and this set happened to have several of the hardest movements for me personally so I’m proud I knocked it out.

Managed to do my last set of squats at 135lbs which I’m super happy with after not squatting at all for a few months.

📽 @lauras_fit_to_live
